            <title>[OPENJPA-1559] DataCacheManager initialization isn&apos;t thread safe.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1559</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running normally, some of OpenJPA configuration is lazily loaded and is not thread safe. Normally this isn&apos;t an issue if one thread has a different configured object than another.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Today I came across a problem when using the DataCache EvictionScheduler that multiple scheduler threads can get created and kicked off. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
